Function Reference/wp unique post slug « WordPress Codex
-----------

Computes a unique slug for the post, when given the desired slug and
some post details.

Usage
-----

` <?php wp_unique_post_slug( $slug, $post_ID, $post_status, $post_type, $post_parent ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$slug` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) the desired slug (post\_name)
    Default: *None*

 `$post_ID` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*)
    Default: *None*

 `$post_status` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) no uniqueness checks are made if the post is still
    draft or pending
    Default: *None*

 `$post_type` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*)
    Default: *None*

 `$post_parent` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*)
    Default: *None*

Return Values
-------------

 `` `(string)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   unique slug for the post, based on \$post\_name (with a -1, -2, etc.
    suffix)

Change Log
----------

Since: [2.8](/Version_2.8 "Version 2.8")

Source File
-----------

`wp_unique_post_slug()` is located in `wp-includes/post.php`

